<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-194-218  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 194 218.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  April 17 1989 n311 p102(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Wise VARs to reap rewards. (value-added resellers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cooley, Ross.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The trend of mergers, consolidations and bankruptcies seen amongvalue-added resellers (VARs) in 1988 is expected to continue in1989.andP;  To grow and prosper a VAR will have to plan to providesolutions for specific markets which are just emerging.andO;Specialization and differentiation from other VARs will give a VARa competitive advantage.andP;  Desktop publishing has been one marketin which VARs have not been unable to distinguish themselvesbecause of the lack of differentiation of bundled desktoppublishing packages.andP;  Computer-aided design and engineering andworkgroup computing are areas that promise continued growth in thefuture.andP;  In 1989 the 80386 processor segment of the market willshow over 100 percent growth.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Value-Added ResellersMarket SegmentationOutlookGrowthIndustry AnalysisSpecializationCompetitionMarketing Strategy.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>